PROGRAM 1

Install C Compiler in Virtual Machine Using VirtualBox and Execute Simple Programs

Requirements
Oracle VirtualBox
Ubuntu OVA File
GCC Compiler

Step 1 Open VirtualBox

1. Open VirtualBox application.
2. Wait for VirtualBox Manager window.

Step 2 Import Ubuntu OVA File

1. Click File.
2. Click Import Appliance.
3. Browse and select ubuntu_gt6.ova.
4. Click Next.
5. Click Import.
6. Wait until import completes.

Step 3 Configure USB Settings

1. Select imported Ubuntu VM.
2. Click Settings.
3. Open USB.
4. Select USB 1.1.
5. Click OK.

Step 4 Start Ubuntu VM

1. Select VM.
2. Click Start.
3. Wait for Ubuntu login screen.

Step 5 Login
Username dinesh
Password 99425

Step 6 Open Terminal

1. Open Ubuntu search.
2. Search Terminal.
3. Open Terminal.

Step 7 Navigate Directory
Type
cd /opt/axis2/axis2-1.7.3/bin

Step 8 Create C Program
Type
gedit hello.c

Enter program
#include<stdio.h>
int main()
{
printf("Hello World");
return 0;
}

Save file.

Step 9 Compile Program
Type
gcc hello.c

Step 10 Execute Program
Type
./a.out

Result
Thus simple C program executed successfully.

